{"body": "If you absolutely need to use Models, why not simply define them in the Migration itself?\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nclass ChangeProducts < ActiveRecord::Migration\r\n  class SampleProduct < ActiveRecord::Base\r\n    self.table_name = \"products\"\r\n  end\r\n\r\n  def up\r\n    SampleProduct.update_all(valid: true)\r\n  end\r\n\r\n  def down\r\n    # ...\r\n  end\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nI don't think we should promote the usage of models in Migrations with a specific API, if you need them, it's very easy to define them. I'm :-1: on this one.\r\n\r\n/cc @rafaelfranca @carlosantoniodasilva ", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/15948359", "created_at": "2013-04-05T10:18:16Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9959#issuecomment-15948359", "updated_at": "2013-04-05T10:18:16Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 9959, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/senny", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/3d698e2872c07061a455d9e250861235?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fd1359f9934ee5a75ed441ffce412a0a1.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/received_events", "gravatar_id": "3d698e2872c07061a455d9e250861235", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "senny", "type": "User", "id": 5402, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237e530bd3543c15100933f"}, "id": 15948359, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/9959"}
